Capitalism and socialism are no longer regarded as irreconcilable opposites . Bulgaria has been pursuing an active policy of good-neighbourliness and mutual understanding . Bulgaria is pursuing a consistent policy designed to develop bilateral and multilateral economic co-operation .

The Yemen Arab Republic reiterates its full support for the total elimination of nuclear weapons by the nuclear-weapon States by the end of this century . Yemen also supports the repeated calls for banning nuclear-weapons tests and diverting the tremendous expenditures freed thereby to economic and social development in the interest of mankind . The halting and banning of nuclear tests is one of the priorities of nuclear disarmament .

President Manuel Pinto da Costa congratulates Nigeria's President on his election to preside over the forty-fourth session of the U.N. General Assembly . Praises the Secretary-General for his far-sightedness, his constant efforts and the courage with which he has been seeking solutions to some of the regional conflicts affecting the world .

This month marks 50 years since the Nazi attack on Poland, the Second World War broke out . A living memory of the past is essential in our efforts to shape the world of the future . The end of the war saw the birth of the United Nations, but the years following that war did not bring the ideals that had been fought for . The struggle against poverty, malnutrition and underdevelopment is far from being won, Bach says .

Vanuatu congratulates Nigeria's President on his election to the U.N. General Assembly . The Prime Minister sends his fondest regards to you, a friend and a man he knows to be not only a proud son of Nigeria, but also a proud . son of the Republic of Nigeria . The honorary title of Chief was bestowed upon you at a custom ceremony during a visit you made to Vanuatus in 1985, in your capacity as Chairman of the United Nations Special Committee against Apartheid .

Bolivian President Bolivia congratulates U.N. Secretary-General on assumption of presidency of the current session of the General Assembly . Bolivians want to be able to believe in something important transcending boundaries, he says . Bolivia has managed to honour and pay almost 30 per cent of its foreign debt - money owed to the international banking system .

Papua New Guinea congratulates Nigeria's Garba Garba on his election to the post of President of the General Assembly . The South Pacific is not immune from the effects of international tensions elsewhere and the worrying trends in the world economy . New Caledonia is on the United Nations list of Non-Self Governing Territories, following a decision of the Assembly in December 1986 .

Solomon Islands congratulates Mr. Garba on his election to presidency of the forty-fourth session of the U.N. General Assembly . We are heartened to note that with common sense prevailing the United Nations is at the forefront of international efforts to secure our collective desire for a better and peaceful world .

Ex-Foreign Minister of Nigeria congratulates him on election as President of the U.N. General Assembly . He says the natural sources of life are increasingly being jeopardized . The inviolability of borders is the basis of peaceful relations in Europe . Reforms in Central and Eastern Europe are in the interests of all Europe and of the world .

The General Assembly should consider and adopt concrete measures concerning the observance by all States of the principles of peaceful coexistence among States with different social and political systems . The arms race has been going on, especially in the field of the development and modernization of nuclear arms and of other arms of mass destruction . Romania stands for the cessation of all conflicts in different parts of the world on the basis of equitable solutions . Romania is fully aware of the consequences of the current state of affairs in the world economy .

His Royal Highness Samdech Norodom Sihanouk addressed the Assembly at its forty-fourth session . He paid a heartfelt tribute to his distinguished predecessor, Mr Dante Caputo of Argentina, for his great competence and wisdom, which made it possible for him to conduct the work of the forty-third session of the General Assembly .

President of the forty-fourth session of the U.N. General Assembly has been elected . Tunisia confirms that it will dedicate itself whole-heartedly to work for the attainment of the ideals of the United Nations . Tunisia was greatly relieved when a cease-fire was reached between Iraq and Iran in conformity with Security Council resolution 598 (1987)

In 1985, soon after taking office, Brazil was emerging from a long night . It was recovering from tragedy and facing great uncertainties . Four years later I see a different political landscape: conflicts have been reduced and dialogue resumed . But we are still far from a world free from anguish, tension and fear . Guerrilla movements are proliferating in several countries .

1989 has been a year of consolidation of the much-enhanced role of the U.N. in international affairs . Namibia's independence will signify the end of the South African regime's illegal occupation of that country . India is concerned at the blood-bath in Afghanistan, which has continued even after the Soviet Union completed the withdrawal of its troops on schedule .

Indonesia is deeply distressed over the continuing tragedy in Lebanon and the grievous loss of lives and material destruction resulting from the resurgence of sectarian and factional strife . Indonesia is committed to the dismantling of institutionalised racism in South Africa so that in its place a non-racial and democratic society can be built . The world's human, technological and material resources are being siphoned away from development purposes, resulting paradoxically in greater overall insecurity .

This year we mark the fiftieth anniversary of the start of the Second World War . The founding and sustaining inspiration of this Organization has been a vision of world peace . The thaw in the climate of East-West relations in recent years has had a profoundly positive effect on the work of the United Nations . The dark days when action was impeded by political point-scoring or capricious use of the veto, appear to be coming to an end .

On 4 October 1973, 16 years ago to the day, I addressed the General Assembly for the first time . The message I carry to this Assembly is first and foremost a message of peace and an appeal for the solidarity of peoples . Our continent needs no armed conflict. It is peace and development to which it deeply aspires .

Forty-five years ago Honduran President Jose Azcona signed the United Nations Charter . He says faith in the organisation has survived intact but has grown because of its achievements . Honduras is convinced that it will continue to play a crucial role in the attainment of our common goals .

Equatorial Guinea delegation expresses satisfaction at election of Nigeria's Garba Garba to direct the work of this session of the General Assembly . Tributes must be paid to Secretary-General Javier Perez de Cuellar and his staff for their efforts in the last ten years to solve the problems that are disrupting peace in various parts of our planet .

Fiji is committed to permanent and secure peace in our world . Fiji was shocked to learn of the assassination of Mr. Jean Marie Tjibaou with his Deputy, Mr. Yeiwene . The South Pacific is a relatively calm and peaceful region . But France continues to carry out nuclear testing in the region .

50 years ago this month, as the Secretary-General reminds us in the introduction to his annual report, world war began in Europe . We must still work for the resolution of conflicts, an end to the arms race and promotion of human rights and development . As we emerge from the shadows of the cold war, our hopes are greater than at any time since the United Nations was formed .

Algeria welcomes election to presidency of the General Assembly at its forty-fourth session . Algeria reaffirms its commitment to that concept of world peace, which should be universal and global in its approach . Algeria hopes for a consolidation of the current cease-fire in order to promote dialogue in mutual respect and in the mutual interests of the parties .

The United Nations was established forty-four years ago upon the ashes of war and amidst great hopes . The UN is not perfect, it is not a panacea for the world's problem, but it is a vital forum where nations seek to replace conflict with consensus, and it must remain a forum for peace . For the sake of mankind, we must halt and reverse this threat .

The Kingdom of Lesotho and the people of the country offer their warm congratulations . They also pay tribute to predecessor, Mr Dante Caputo, for the able and effective manner in which he conducted the proceedings of the forty-third session . For far too long, the world has failed to muster sufficient political will to reverse the ever-rising tide of inequalities among and within nations .

The Gambia congratulates Mr. Garba on his election as President of the forty-fourth session of the U.N. General Assembly . It is regrettable that the notable achievements made in the resolution of regional conflicts are not reflected in the situation in southern Africa . Attempts at appeasing, persuading or pampering the racist Pretoria regime in order to make it change its policy can only fortify that regime .

For the first time in this century, we have a situation in which the struggle for peace and justice within nations makes understanding between super-Powers possible . Latin America has set in motion various efforts at political co-operation aimed at implementing concrete proposals relating to the security of the hemisphere, the consolidation of democracy, the maintenance of peace, and the problems of international trade and the foreign debt .

The German Democratic Republic believes the authority and influence of the U.N. will have to be brought into play more effectively than has been the case so far . Economic underdevelopment must be overcome and the natural environment preserved for man to exist, he says . The existence of two sovereign German States is of great importance for stability in Europe and detente in the world .

The dream of a free Namibia needs to be realized with the full implementation of the U.N. plan for the Independence; of Namibia . The return to Namibia, after 30 years of exile, of Sam Nujoma, the courageous nationalist, augurs well and should be a positive step for peace in that country .

The practice of multilateral diplomacy is now inevitable, and it is essential that we adopt a collective approach in dealing with the problems before us . The Arab-Israeli conflict, at the core of which is the question of Palestine, remains the most serious and the one most urgently requiring solution . Jordan's objective in its endeavours to address the question has been, and continues to be, to achieve a just peace settlement .

The Congo welcomes the 'wind of change' that has been blowing throughout the world for some time now, fostering dialogue between the United States and the Soviet Union . The People's Republic of the Congo has excellent relations of friendship, brotherhood and co-operation with the United Nations .

Nigeria's President congratulates him on his election as President of the U.N. General Assembly . He also pays tribute to his predecessor in office, Mr. Dante Caputo of Argentina, for the exemplary manner in which he guided the affairs of this Assembly during the forty-third session .

It is now ten years since democracy was re-established in Ecuador and a year since President Rodrigo Borja assumed his constitutional mandate . The threat of confrontation has not been eliminated, nor has a solution been found to all regional conflicts . Leaders of Latin America want a negotiated political solution to the Panama crisis .

Israeli authorities' treatment of the Palestinian Arab people is the greatest threat to any peace plan, he says . 'Peace is still an aspiration that Israel rejects, and it continues to place obstacles in the way of its attainment' 'Invasion and occupation are not acceptable; they are intolerable, and must be brought to an end as quickly as possible'

The elimination of apartheid in South Africa is a prime responsibility of our Organization and of the international community . Qatar considers the elimination of South Africa to be a lofty goal for all mankind . We hope this conference will provide solutions conducive to the protection of our planet . We also support the establishment of nuclear-weapon-free zones, particularly in the Indian Ocean and the Middle East .

Seychelles supports the proposal to levy an international tax on pollution . Revenue would go to finance environmental protection programmes of developing countries . Small island States in particular have little means of countering this problem, writes minister . He urges solidarity on the part of the international community to see that these proposals are translated into deeds .

The Ethiopian delegation expresses its support for the President of the General Assembly at its forty-fourth session . The relaxation of tension in world politics over the past two years has justified that outlook . The commencement of the implementation of the United Nations plan for the independence of Namibia is a testimony to the capacity of the U.N. to discharge such important responsibilities when there exists the appropriate international environment .

Government of Trinidad and Tobago expresses concern over attempts by the apartheid regime to frustrate the electoral process set out in Security Council resolution 435 (1978) South Africa must not obtain by devious means what it could not achieve by naked force, says the Government . Despite progress in Namibia, apartheid still exists in neighbouring South Africa .

President of the Republic of Nigeria expresses his 'deep pleasure' at being present in the General Assembly . Paraguay expresses hope that by following the broad highway of liberty and justice they may bring peace and prosperity to all mankind . The tragedy of Tiananmen Square and the executions ordered by people's courts also deserve our most sincere and heartfelt repugnance .

As of 27 September 1989 there does not remain a single volunteer Vietnamese soldier in Cambodia - either army man, adviser or military employee . The total withdrawal of Vietnamese troops from Cambodia is an important and fundamental contribution on the peaceful settlement of the Cambodian question . We stand for convening of an international conference on the Middle East with the participation of all patties concerned and of Palestine on an equal footing .

I was Deputy Prime Minister of a recently elected Labour Government in 1985 . I spoke on behalf of New Zealand in the general debate during the fortieth session . Failure to make progress on nuclear disarmament had distorted the fabric of international life . New Zealand is disappointed that the United Nations plays a less than central role in key disarmament negotiations .

Panama hopes that the community of nations will weigh the potential consequences of a heightening of the United States military threat against my country . Panama's defence forces in no way represent a traditional army organized as a repressive force; on the contrary, they are a genuine expression of our people . Panama would be willing to accept the headquarters of such a multinational force in our territory .

The Malawi delegation congratulates Ambassador Garba on his election to the president of the General Assembly . They also congratulate his predecessor, Mr. Dante Caputo, former Minister of Foreign Affairs of Argentina, on the effective manner in which he presided over the forty-third session . We are more than confident that under his leadership and guidance the Assembly will be able to achieve success by aiming for pragmatic resolutions .

It would be inconsistent with moral justice and social equity if the improved climate of East-West relations bred complacency and neglect of third-world issues . The world continues to seethe under the enduring effects of the thorniest areas of contention, despite the improvement in the international political climate . The international community must continue to intensify its pressure for the total abolition of apartheid .

The People's Republic of Benin supports the rapprochement between the United States and the Soviet Union . Disarmament remains the surest way today of creating an atmosphere conducive to the establishment of lasting peace in the world . Benin is ready to support any measures aimed at drafting an international convention on the protection and conservation of the world's climate .

Somalia has close brotherly ties with Nigeria, which continues to play a leading role in furthering the purposes and principles of the United Nations Charter . Somalia believes that most of the developing countries continue to remain outside the mainstream of progress achieved in the world economy in recent years . The international community is under a moral obligation to continue to provide the refugees with the humanitarian assistance .

The climate of co-operation and accommodation between the two super-Powers has had global ramifications and augurs well for the gradual elimination of tensions . The assassination of a prominent SWAPO member, Mr. Anton Luborski, in Windhoek, underscores our expressed concern for the security of the leadership off SWAPo . We call for the withdrawal of all foreign forces from the area in order to pave the way for the success of the intercommunal talks .

Recent developments in the international situation give us cause for optimism . Cape Verde pays tribute to the Governments of the U.S. and the Soviet Union for the renewed hope of peace that the detente in their relations has brought to mankind . Peace must be based on a correct evaluation and solution of the problem of underdevelopment .

The Bahamas is confident that your vast experience and reputation as an outstanding diplomat will greatly facilitate your work at this session and enhance its success . We are at a significant crossroads in human affairs, at which we must both reflect on the successes and the frustrations of the 1980s and look forward optimistically to the challenges of the 1990s .
